(82,	'Request for Police Protection',	'<p>Botswana Police Service in its mandate articulated that the service   shall be employed in and throughout Botswana to protect life and   property, prevent and detect crime, repress internal disturbances,   maintain security and public tranquility. Dully enforce all written laws   with which it is charged and generally maintain peace.  The Police provide an over dimensional escort service for commercial   businesses where the transit of vehicles, animals, goods or equipment   may affect road safety or disrupt the flow of traffic.</p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n  <li>Political rallies</li>\r\n  <li>Demonstrations/petitions</li>\r\n  <li>Sponsored walk</li>\r\n  <li>Sporting activities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Prior arrangement with relevant authorities should always be made so   that deployment can be arranged well on time before the commencement of   the event.</p>',	'Request for Police Protection',	'mcms',	'Main Pages',	'2017-11-14',	'',	'Active',	'',	'bps-content.php?cid=82',	NULL,	'',	'19:54:28',	0,	NULL,	'',	''),
(83,	'Request for Police Escort/Coverage',	'<p>\r\n	Botswana Police Service provides escort or coverage where there is public gathering. The escort/coverage may be requested from the nearest Police Station and is subject to approval. The escort is provided to;</p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Political rallies</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Demonstrations/petitions</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Sponsored walk</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Sporting activities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	'Request for Police Escort/Coverage',	'mcms',	'Main Pages',	'2017-11-14',	'',	'Active',	'',	'bps-content.php?cid=83',	NULL,	'',	'19:55:26',	0,	NULL,	'',	''),
(84,	'Mediation Services',	'<p>\r\n	The Police Service is not only interested in criminal related issues, but a wide range of issues that the members of the public would like to be assisted with. The Police are involved in mediation of disputes emanating from misunderstanding. Members of the public are encouraged to always come forth to the Police whenever they have disputes of any kind so as to seek mediation from the Police. There are Social Welfare Officers based in at all the Police Stations who can help them solve their problems amicably.</p>\r\n',	'Mediation Services',	'mcms',	'Main Pages',	'2017-11-14',	'',	'Active',	'',	'bps-content.php?cid=84',	NULL,	'',	'19:56:38',	0,	NULL,	'',	''),
(85,	'Reporting a Missing Person',	'<p>A person is reported missing after 48 hours, and when making a report the following information should be given to the Police.</p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n  <li>Names and age of the missing person </li>\r\n  <li>Description of the missing person and mental status (sex, colour,   height, body marks like tattoos, scars or any outstanding feature and   what they were last seen wearing). </li>\r\n  <li>Date and time he/she left home </li>\r\n  <li>Photos can also be brought along. If a person is reported missing   and at a later stage found, the police should be notified of such   recovery.</li>\r\n</ul>',	'Reporting a Missing Person',	'mcms',	'Main Pages',	'2017-11-14',	'',	'Active',	'',	'bps-content.php?cid=85',	NULL,	'',	'19:57:48',	0,	NULL,	'',	''),
