(95,	'Car Import / Export Clearance',	'<p>\r\n	An official document prepared by the Police after vetting of vehicles</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>How can I obtain the service?</strong><br />\r\n	Bring the following to designated Police Stations:</p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Vehicle to be cleared</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Original documents pertaining to the vehicle plus two copies</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		National Identity Card or passport</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	For new vehicles bring one of the following documents:</p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Invoice</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Invoice and <strong>SARPCCO</strong> clearance certificate (<strong>SARPCCO</strong> Southern African Regional Police Chiefs Coordination Organisation)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Invoice and SARPCCO clearance certificate and Registration Book</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Invoice and Registration Book</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	For <strong>used</strong> Motor Vehicles bring the following documents:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>SARPCCO Countries</strong></p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Registration Book and SARPCCO clearance certificate (Foreigners)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Invoice, SARPCCO clearance certificate, Registration Book (Batswana and Temporary residents)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		SARPCCO Clearance Certificate is valid for three months. After the expiry date a new certificate has to be requested from the originating country by the applicant.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Non SARPCCO Countries</strong></p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Invoice</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Bill of lading (Imports. e.g. Japan, Singapore etc)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Can I apply for the service online</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Service is currently unavailable online</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Costs involved in obtaining the service.</strong><br />\r\n	Currently the service is free.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Where can I find the service</strong>?</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The service can be obtained from the following Police Stations:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\\\"text-align:left\\\">\r\n	<p>\r\n		Serious Crime Squad<br />\r\n		P.O. Box 1082<br />\r\n		Gaborone<br />\r\n		Tel: (+267) 3956999/3952531/3911892</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		Woodhall Police Station<br />\r\n		P.O. Box 89<br />\r\n		Lobatse<br />\r\n		Tel: (+267) 5333012</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		Serowe Police Station<br />\r\n		P.O. Box 255<br />\r\n		Serowe<br />\r\n		Tel: (+267) 4630222</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		&nbsp;</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		Mahalapye Police Station<br />\r\n		P.O. Box 31<br />\r\n		Mahalapye<br />\r\n		Tel: (+267) 4710222</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		Selebi Phikwe Police Station<br />\r\n		P.O. Box 15<br />\r\n		Selebi Phikwe<br />\r\n		Tel: (+267) 2610301</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		Criminal Investigation Department (North)<br />\r\n		P.O. Box 91<br />\r\n		Francistown<br />\r\n		Tel: (+267) 2423000</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		Maun Police Station<br />\r\n		P. O. Box 7<br />\r\n		Maun<br />\r\n		Tel: (+267) 6860034</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		Kasane Police Station<br />\r\n		P. O. Box 1<br />\r\n		Kasane<br />\r\n		Tel: (+267) 6250326</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		Gantsi Police Station<br />\r\n		P. O. Box 26<br />\r\n		Gantsi<br />\r\n		Tel: (+267) 6596222</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		Tsabong Police Station<br />\r\n		P. O. Box 3<br />\r\n		Tsabong<br />\r\n		Tel: (+267) 6540423</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		&nbsp;</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<strong>Business Hours</strong><br />\r\n		Monday to Friday<br />\r\n		0730 hours &ndash; 1245 hours<br />\r\n		1345 hours &ndash; 1630 hours</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		The service is not available during weekends and public holidays.</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<strong>Where can I find more information?</strong><br />\r\n		Contact:Officer Commanding<br />\r\n		Serious Crime Squad<br />\r\n		P.O. Box 1082, Gaborone.<br />\r\n		Tel: (+267) 3956999/3952531/3911892<br />\r\n		Service Branches:<br />\r\n		You may locate the service branche in charge in the &nbsp;<br />\r\n		<a h