(111,	'Ground breaking ceremony for Maitengwe Police Station',	'Speaking at the event, Minister of Infrastructure and Housing Development Mr Nonofo Molefhi urged contactors to complete the project in time to save money for the government. The Minister said contractors have a tendency of failing to complete government projects, explaining that the government does not tolerate such. He said upon completion, the project will make a difference in the lives of people in the village adding that challenges of cross border crime will be addressed. He said the police station will cost the government P75 million and will be completed in May 2019.\r\nFor his part, the Minister of Defence, Justice and Security, Mr Shaw Kgathi said the construction of the police station will help to fight crime such as employing illegal immigrants, stock theft, house breaking and theft which are a concern in the area. He said upon completion of the police station, police officers will be increased from three to 50 to combat crime.\r\nGiving vote of thanks, the Member of Parliament for the area Honuorable Edwin Batshu said Maitengwe residents are greatful of the developments in their village. Mr Batshu said the project will create employment for people in his constituency. He thanked the government for bringing such developments to his constituency saying that the construction of the police station will help in the fight against crime that occurs between Botswana and neighbouring countries.\r\n',	NULL,	'breakingnews',	NULL,	'2017-11-20',	NULL,	'no',	'no',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	'14:44:36',	0,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
