(130,	'Branches',	'<h3>\r\n	Development Finance and Procurement</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Manages the administration of the Botswana Police Service ensuring that budgeting, procurement, disbursement, administration and management of supplies of the organisation recurrent budget in accordance with the finance regulations and procedures. It is also responsible for the planning, development and maintenance of the Botswana Police Service Estate and Facilities.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The branch is formed by the following Units;</p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Development and Planning</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Finance</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Quarter Master and Procurement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\\\"well\\\">\r\n	<h4 class=\\\"redtxt\\\">\r\n		For more information contact:</h4>\r\n	<h4>\r\n		Director Development Finance and Procurement</h4>\r\n	<div class=\\\"row\\\">\r\n		<div class=\\\"col-md-4\\\">\r\n			<p>\r\n				<strong>Postal Address: </strong><br />\r\n				P/Bag 0012<br />\r\n				Gaborone</p>\r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\\\"col-md-4\\\">\r\n			<p>\r\n				<strong>Physical Address: </strong><br />\r\n				Police Headquarters<br />\r\n				Government Enclave,<br />\r\n				Gaborone</p>\r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\\\"col-md-4\\\">\r\n			<p>\r\n				<strong>Contact :</strong></p>\r\n			<p>\r\n				<strong>Phone: </strong>3951161<br />\r\n				<strong>Fax: </strong>3973723</p>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Department of Management Services</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Departmental Management Services Branch manages, directs and develops a diverse range of key corporate management functions and services which include Legal Services, Training, Administration and Human Resources Management for the entire Botswana Police Service to enhance the achievement of its goals and objectives. The following units fall under the branch:</p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Human Resources Unit</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Occupational health and safety Unit</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Salaries and welfare</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Legal services Unit</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Training and Development Unit</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Internal affairs Unit</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Youth office</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Pensions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>\r\n	Its key functions include</h4>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Recruitment and selection</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Career development and succession planning</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Manpower Planning</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		HIV/AIDS Prevention, Care and Support</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Occupational Health and Safety Management</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Employee Social Welfare Management</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Chaplaincy Programme</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Facilitates the assessment of guardianship of minor dependants of deceased officers by monitoring the communication with the legal representatives and recommendations of the guardians as per the rules of the Fund.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Receives, investigates and answers beneficiaries and member related queries.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Ensures that all officers who retire, resign and those who are dismissed complete notification forms in time to facilitate the speedy processing of benefits/pension.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\\\"well\\\">\r\n	<div class=\\\"row\\\">\r\n		<div class=\\\"col-md-6\\\">\r\n			<p>\r\n				<strong>Postal Address:</strong><br />\r\n				P/Bag 0012<br />\r\n				Gaborone</p>\r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\\\"col-md-6\\\">\r\n			<p>\r\n				<strong>Physical Address:</strong><br />\r\n				Police Headquarters<br />\r\n				Government Enclave,<br />\r\n				Gaborone</p>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Police College</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Botswana Police College is situated along Gaborone Lobatse road. The College is set out on a backdrop of Lentswe la Baratani Hill between Otse and Mogobane villages. The College is registered with Botswana Training Authority (BOTA) as a tertiary institution and also accredited to Portsmouth University in England. The College provides training, development, consultancy and research to produce officers compatible to national and international standards. At the end of 12 months training, trainees are awarded certificates. The College also offers in-service courses. As a result of the merge of the Botswana Police Service with Botswana Local Police Force, the then Local Police College, THE CENTRE in Kanye was incorporated in to Botswana Police College and it offers in-service courses.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Police College also houses&nbsp;the International Law Enforcement Academy (ILEA) established by Botswana and the United States of America in 2000 to promote international cooperation against crime.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The units that form the police college are :</p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Police Clinic</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Traffic and Driver Training Unit</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Detective Training Unit</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Policing and Management Unit</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Quality Assurance Unit</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Quality Assurance Roles</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Botswana Police College Accredited Programmes</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		College Training Standards</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		International programmes unit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Recruitment and Selection</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	The following are the Requirement for Pre-Service Training:</p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Candidates must be aged between 18 and 30 years,</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Having passed BGCSE with a Credit in English Language and minimum overall of 30 points for the best 6 subjects including English.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		In case of Special Constables with at least two years of services they should also have a BGCSE Certificate of at least 28 points and a pass in English.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Having good character</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Without any criminal record</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Physically and mentally fit (confirmed by a Government Medical Doctor).</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		They should be citizens of Botswana.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Vacant posts are advertised in the local media (news papers) and candidates show their interest by making written applications to Director of Training, Botswana Police College, Private Bag 009, Otse, Botswana.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Courses taught include :</p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Criminal Law</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Statute Law</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Criminal Procedure and Evidence</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Police Duties</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Criminology</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Computer Awareness and Crime Criminal Recording System (CCRS)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Communication and Study Skills</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Physical Education</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		A month attachment on the field.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Police College provides a professional health care service (clinic) to the College community, and the public. The following are the services provided by police clinic:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Preventative, restorative services &nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		(Consultation and treatment) offered by Nurses &amp; the Doctor</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Pharmaceutical services</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Laboratory services (wide range including HIV screening)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Radiology services</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Sexual and Reproductive Health (SRH) services</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Child Welfare</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Emergency care</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Other pending services are Labour and delivery, Minor operations and Safe male&nbsp; circumcision</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\\\"redtxt\\\">\r\n	<strong>For more information Contact:</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Director of Training<br />\r\n	Tel: 5336200<br />\r\n	Fax: 5337529</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Transport and Telecommunication Branch(TTB)</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	TTB is a branch established to ensure availability of Transport and Communication services to members of the Botswana Police Service. The Branch supports the organisation with technologies intended to assist BPS carry out its mandate.<br />\r\n	The Branch has four main units as follows:</p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Transport Unit</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Telecommunications South</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Telecommunications North</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Information Technology Unit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\\\"well\\\">\r\n	<div class=\\\"row\\\">\r\n		<div class=\\\"col-md-5\\\">\r\n			<p>\r\n				<strong>For more information contact</strong>:<br />\r\n				Director Transport and Telecommunication<br />\r\n				P/Bag X07<br />\r\n				Village,Gaborone</p>\r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\\\"col-md-4\\\">\r\n			<p>\r\n				<strong>Physical Address:</strong><br />\r\n				Metsemotlhabe road,<br />\r\n				Old Police College,<br />\r\n				Village<br />\r\n				Gaborone</p>\r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\\\"col-md-3\\\">\r\n			<p>\r\n				Phone: 3605500<br />\r\n				Inquiries: 3957269<br />\r\n				Fax: 3900296</p>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Special Support Group</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Special Support Group (SSG) is a para-military Branch of the Botswana Police Service (BPS). It was formed in 1978 when the Police Mobile Unit (PMU) that existed in the early 1970s was disbanded to form the nuclear of the Botswana Defence Force (BDF) in 1977. SSG was born with a total strength of thirty-four (34) officers of different ranks. Its strength increased by 121 from 1980 and 1983 and increased to 569 between 1984 and 1991 and to 807 between 1991 to 1994. In 1990 it was transformed into companies, platoons and sections for easy command and control. It provides operational support to Divisions, Districts and Stations by;</p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Mobile and foot patrols</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Escort/shipment of revenue and minerals</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Escort of hardened criminals from State Prison to places of trial</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		VIP Protection</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Border Patrols</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Crime surveillance</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Provision of security at political meetings, sports activities and demonstrations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	It also compliments with the following specialized services</p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Public order operations</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Tracking operations</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Narcotic searches</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Peace Keeping Missions</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Disposal of explosives like bombs</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Rescue operations</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Scuba divers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\\\"well\\\">\r\n	<div class=\\\"row\\\">\r\n		<div class=\\\"col-md-6\\\">\r\n			<p>\r\n				<strong>For more information contact:</strong><br />\r\n				The Commander Special Support Group<br />\r\n				P O Box 40116&nbsp;<br />\r\n				Gaborone</p>\r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\\\"col-md-6\\\">\r\n			<p>\r\n				Fax: 3903305<br />\r\n				Tel: 3912081<br />\r\n				Inquiries: 3957272</p>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Air Support Services</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Air Support Branch was formed in January 2009 to enhance efficiency and effectiveness of the Botswana Police Service operations around the country. Support and work with other branches within the Botswana Police Service to execute the following duties:</p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Prevention and Investigation operation</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Rapid response to crime incidents</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Aerial photographs and videos</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Monitoring of public gatherings and events</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Border patrols</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Searching for missing persons</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Critical incidents /disaster management (rescue)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\\\"well\\\">\r\n	<div class=\\\"row\\\">\r\n		<div class=\\\"col-md-6\\\">\r\n			<p>\r\n				<strong>For more information contact: </strong><br />\r\n				Director Air Support<br />\r\n				Tel: 3915388<br />\r\n				Fax: 3973723</p>\r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\\\"col-md-6\\\">\r\n			<p>\r\n				Postal Address:<br />\r\n				P/Bag SK8<br />\r\n				Gaborone</p>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Criminal Investigations Department</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Criminal Investigation Department (CID) is a Branch in the Botswana Police Service that prevents and detects crime and is responsible for the investigation of serious crimes.<br />\r\n	CID consists of specialised units such as Serious Crime Squad,&nbsp;<strong>Diamond and Minerals Protection,</strong>Narcotic,&nbsp;Fauna and Flora&nbsp;Investigation, Crime Prevention, National Central Bureau (NCB) and Interpol. The Branch has establishment at Stations, Districts and Divisions.</p>\r\n<h4 class=\\\"redtxt\\\">\r\n	For more information contact</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	Director<br />\r\n	Criminal Investigation Department<br />\r\n	Phone: 3914706<br />\r\n	Fax: 3952651<br />\r\n	Box 1082, Gaborone<br />\r\n	Enquiries: 3642300</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Traffic Branch</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Traffic Branch is responsible for ensuring the safety of all those who use the roads. The mandate is to make the roads safer by reducing fatal, serious, minor injuries and the protection of property damage caused by motor vehicle crashes. The roles include;</p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Assisting all road users in need and to reassure those in difficulties</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Educating members of the public on road safety</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Facilitating the free flow of traffic</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Enforcing the Road Traffic Act/Regulations and all other laws</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>For more information contact:</strong><br />\r\n	Director, Traffic<br />\r\n	Tel: 3624039<br />\r\n	Fax: 3910044</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Crime Intelligence Branch</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Crime Intelligence Branch (CRIB)&nbsp;was formed in 2002 to gather crime intelligence.&nbsp;It provides a number of services to operational law enforcement to enhance the development of criminal intelligence on serious criminality. CRIB also conducts research and analysis on a range of specialist areas.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The following are the functions of the Branch</p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Gather, correlate, evaluate and analyse information on criminal activities.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Identify any potential or existing threat to the security of the country or its people.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Effectively monitor the activities of persons, and organisations suspected of engaging in an organised criminal enterprise, and of persons and organizations suspected of conducting or planning violent acts against the citizens of the country.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Study crime incidents, identify and analyse crime patterns, crime trends and crime problems.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\\\"well\\\">\r\n	<div class=\\\"row\\\">\r\n		<div class=\\\"col-md-4\\\">\r\n			<p>\r\n				<strong>Postal Address:</strong><br />\r\n				P/Bag 0012<br />\r\n				Gaborone</p>\r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\\\"col-md-4\\\">\r\n			<p>\r\n				<strong>Physical Address: </strong><br />\r\n				Police Headquarters<br />\r\n				Government Enclave,<br />\r\n				Gaborone</p>\r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\\\"col-md-4\\\">\r\n			<p>\r\n				Inquiries: 3957058<br />\r\n				Fax: 391 4833</p>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Northern Division</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	This Division existed as early as 1964. It has six (6) Districts namely 1, 5, 7, 8, 10 and 15 comprising of thirty two (32) Police Stations its headquarters is located in Francistown.&nbsp; Below are the Police Districts and stations that it covers;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>No. 1 District</strong><br />\r\n	Kutlwano, Tonota, Tatitown, Gerald and Matsiloje&nbsp;Police Station.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>No. 5 District</strong><br />\r\n	Maun, Seronga, Sehitwa, Gumare and Shakwe&nbsp;Police Station</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>No. 7 District</strong><br />\r\n	Kasane, Kasane Airport, Pandamatenga, Kazungula, and Kachikau&nbsp;Police Station</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>No. 8 District</strong><br />\r\n	Letlhakane, Orapa, Dukwi, Rakops and Sowa&nbsp;Police Station</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>No. 10 District</strong><br />\r\n	Selibe Phikwe, Botshabelo, Bainesdrift, Semolale and Bobonong Police stations.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>No. 15 District</strong><br />\r\n	Francistown ,Tutume, Masunga and Tshesebe Police Station.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>For more information contact :</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Divisional Commander Northern<br />\r\n	Francistown</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Tel: 2414545<br />\r\n	Fax: 2414965</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	South Central Division</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	South Central Division was established in 1997 after the proposal to reorganize the Divisions, of which by then were only two which were North and South Divisions. South Central Division which is headquartered in Broadhurst, Gaborone comprises of five (5) Districts (No. 2, 3, 12, 13 and 16) under which&nbsp;&nbsp;22 Police stations fall. Below are the Police Districts and stations that it covers:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>No. 2 District</strong><br />\r\n	Serowe, Palapye, Maunatlala, and Serule Police stations.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>No. 3 District</strong><br />\r\n	Broadhurst, Central, Urban, Tlokweng and Borakanelo Police Stations.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>No. 12 District</strong><br />\r\n	Mochudi, Sikwane and Oliphantsdrift Police Stations.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>No. 13 District</strong><br />\r\n	Gaborone West, Mogoditshane, Naledi, Sir Seretse Khama Airport (SSKA) and Ramotswa Police Stations.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>No. 16 District</strong><br />\r\n	Mahalapye, Shoshong, Machaneng, Martinsdrift and Dibete.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>For more information contact:</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Divisional South Central Headquarters<br />\r\n	Broadhurst<br />\r\n	Gaborone</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Tel: 3624014<br />\r\n	Fax: 3957453</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Southern Division</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Southern Division is situated in the southern part of Botswana with its headquarters located in Lobatse. The Division is composed of five (5) Police Districts (No&#39;s 4, 6, 9, 11 and 14). There are 25 police stations within this division.&nbsp;Below are the Police Districts and stations that it covers;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>No. 4 District </strong><br />\r\n	Lobatse, Woodhall, Goodhope and Ramatlabama Police Stations.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>No. 6 District </strong><br />\r\n	Gantsi, Charleshill, Kalkfontein and Ncojane Police Stations.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>No. 9 District </strong><br />\r\n	Tsabong, Tshane, Werda, Bokspits, Kang and Middlepits Police Stations.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>No. 11 District </strong><br />\r\n	Molepolole, Letlhakeng, Takatokwane, Thamaga and Sojwe Police Stations.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>No. 14 District </strong><br />\r\n	Kanye, Sejelo, Moshupa, Jwaneng, Phitshane Molopo and Mabutsane Police Stations.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>For more information contact:</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Divisional Commander Southern<br />\r\n	Lobatse</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Tel: 5334453<br />\r\n	Fax: 5330223</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Forensic Science Services</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Forensic Science Services Branch was established in 2006. Its functions are;</p>\r\n<ul class=\\\"listing\\\">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Provides forensic services and management of criminal records</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Provides expert testimony</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Issues clearance certificates</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Analyses and identifies questioned documents</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Provides scientific investigation</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Analyses dagga and other habit forming drugs.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Analyses samples of suspected poisoning cases.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Determination of alcohol levels in cases of drunken driving.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Analyses currency to establish authenticity.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Determination of origin and cause of fire</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Estimates age, gender etc in cases of death</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The Units are;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Criminal Records Bureau</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Forensic Science Laboratory</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Forensic Pathology</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>For more information contact:</strong></p>\r\n<div class=\\\"well\\\">\r\n	<div class=\\\"row\\\">\r\n		<div class=\\\"col-md-4\\\">\r\n			<p>\r\n				<strong>For more information contact: </strong><br />\r\n				Director,<br />\r\n				Forensic Science Services<br />\r\n				P/Bag 0400, Gaborone, Botswana.</p>\r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\\\"col-md-4\\\">\r\n			<p>\r\n				<strong>Physical address: </strong><br />\r\n				Plot 22117 Kgomokasitwa Road,<br />\r\n				Gaborone West Industrial.</p>\r\n		</div>\r\n		<div class=\\\"col-md-4\\\">\r\n			<p>\r\n				Tel: 3918601<br />\r\n				Fax : 3918145/3918615</p>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n',	'Branches',	'mcms',	'15',	'2017-12-05',	NULL,	'Active',	NULL,	'bps-content.php?cid=130',	NULL,	NULL,	'14:28:36',	26,	NULL,	'',	''),
