(183,	'Department of Management Services',	'<p>Departmental Management Services Branch manages, directs and develops a diverse range of key corporate management functions and services which include Legal Services, Training, Administration and Human Resources Management for the entire Botswana Police Service to enhance the achievement of its goals and objectives. The following units fall under the branch;</p>\r\n<h3>Human Resources Unit</h3>\r\n<p>The Human Resources Unit provides effective strategic and operational human resource services; development and implementation of the human resource policies, procedures and programs; training and development recruitment and selection; management of HR Information systems and providing advisory support to line management and staff to facilitate and enhance a constructive and positive work environment in order to meet organizational objectives. It also develops position profiles and career development parts in order to attract and retain suitably qualified and experienced staff. Its key functions include;</p>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>Recruitment and  selection </li>\r\n    <li>Promotions and  Transfers </li>\r\n    <li>Record keeping of all  personal data </li>\r\n    <li>Confidential advice  to internal customer in relation to problems at work </li>\r\n    <li>Career development  and succession planning </li>\r\n    <li>Competency Mapping  (To identify and describe competencies that are most critical to success in a  work situation or work role.) </li>\r\n    <li>Manpower Planning </li>\r\n    <li>Performance Appraisal</li>\r\n  </ul><br/>\r\n\r\n  <p>For further information contact:<br />\r\nHuman Resources Unit<br />\r\nBotswana Police Service<br />\r\n<strong>Tel:</strong> 39551161/3910051/3605513/3605454<br />\r\n<strong>Fax:</strong> 3910081</p>\r\n  <h3>Occupational health and safety Unit</h3>\r\n  <p>The Occupational  Health, Safety, Chaplaincy and Social Welfare (OHSCSW) Unit of the Botswana  Police Service has been established to create a positive healthy, safe,  spiritually and psychosocially supportive work environment for the employees.  Having been established initially as the HIV/AIDS Coordinating Unit in 2003,  the Unit also attended to all health and social welfare issues of employees. It  was then reconstituted into the OHSCSW in 2006 in order to address all human  life issues in the workplace holistically.</p>\r\n  <p><strong>Major components of the  OHSCSW programme</strong></p>\r\n\r\n    <ul>\r\n      <li>HIV/AIDS  Prevention, Care and Support </li>\r\n      <li>Occupational  Health and Safety Management </li>\r\n      <li>Employee  Social Welfare Management </li>\r\n      <li>Chaplaincy  Programme</li>\r\n    </ul><br/>\r\n\r\n    <p><strong>For further information  contact:</strong></p>\r\n    <p>Occupational Health, Safety, Chaplaincy and Social Welfare Unit<br />\r\nBotswana Police Service<br />\r\nPhone:  3951161/3622044/3622114/3622253 <br />\r\nFax: 3973723</p>\r\n    <p><strong>Salaries and welfare</strong></p>\r\n    <p>The Unit is responsible for;</p>\r\n\r\n      <ul>\r\n        <li>Ensuring that the  Botswana Police Service Payroll is effectively maintained. </li>\r\n        <li>Initiates pay and  benefits surveys and constantly monitors group policies and practices to ensure  competitiveness </li>\r\n        <li>Processes workman\'s  compensation claims in the event of employee accidents to expedite the payment  claims. </li>\r\n  </ul><br/>\r\n\r\n<h3>Legal services Unit</h3>\r\n    <p>The Legal Services  Unit mandate is to provide legal and administrative advice to BPS. In so doing  the Unit performs the under listed duties;</p>\r\n    <ul>\r\n      <li>Handling of  complaints by members of the public against the police<strong> </strong> </li>\r\n      <li>Handling of  Affidavits from the Attorney General.<strong> </strong> </li>\r\n      <li>Dealing with personnel  files on legal/administrative issues.<strong> </strong> </li>\r\n      <li>Procurement and  distribution of legal materials within the organisation.<strong> </strong> </li>\r\n      <li>Advising the  organisation on contractual issues.</li>\r\n      <li>Handling of claims against  the police and instructing the Attorney General accordingly.</li>\r\n    </ul><br/>\r\n\r\n	<h3>Training and Development Unit</h3>\r\n    <h3>Mandate</h3>\r\n  <p>Police Training and Development Unit at Police Headquarters exists to complement College efforts in terms meeting manpower development needs of the organization by ensuring that personnel acquire the requisite skills and competencies to competently perform their roles.</p>\r\n\r\n    <h3>Internal affairs Unit</h3>\r\n    <p>The Unit is responsible for  ensuring that the integrity of the Botswana Police Service is maintained through a system of internal discipline where fairness and justice are assured by an objective and impartial investigation and review of cases.</p>\r\n    <h3>Youth office</h3>\r\n    <p>In 2008, the Botswana Police Service established the Youth Office.  Its main objective being to mainstream Youth Work in the organization, establish programmes that will address internal and external youth challenges. We have Youth Focal Person in all Police Stations and Districts to assist youth. The programmes that are currently available are the establishment of anticrime clubs, sports and drama groups.  These initiatives assist youths with something to do with their time as idling can lead to mischief.</p>\r\n    <h3>Pensions</h3>\r\n    <p>The Unit ensures proper administration of the Pension Fund for the  Botswana Police Service in terms of the Pensions Act Cap 27:01, the General  Orders, the Police Act Cap 21:01a and the New Defined Contributory Pension Fund  Regulations</p>\r\n\r\n      <ul>\r\n        <li>Facilitates the  assessment of guardianship of minor dependants of deceased officers by  monitoring the communication with the legal representatives and recommendations  of the guardians as per the rules of the Fund. </li>\r\n        <li>Receives, investigates and answers beneficiaries and member  related queries. <strong></strong></li>\r\n        <li>Ensures that all officers who retire, resign and those who are  dismissed complete notification forms in time to facilitate the speedy  processing of benefits/pension.<strong></strong></li>\r\n      </ul>\r\n\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>',	'Department of Management Services',	'mcms',	'182',	'2011-02-04',	'',	'Active',	'',	'bps-content.php?cid=183',	NULL,	'',	'14:28:16',	0,	0,	'',	''),
(134,	'Development Finance and Procurement',	'<h2>DEVELOPMENT, FINANCE AND PROCUREMENT:</h2>\r\n<p>Manages the administration  of the Unit of the Botswana Police Service ensuring that budgeting,  procurement, disbursement, &nbsp;administration and management of Supplies of  the Botswana Police Service recurrent budget&nbsp;  below the line accounts are done properly and in accordance with the  regulations and procedures and in a way to achieve the&nbsp; goals and objectives.<br />\r\nIt is also responsible for  the planning, development and maintenance of the entire Botswana Police Service  Estate and Facilities as well as ensuring that police officers are issued with  uniform and stationery<strong>. </strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'Development Finance and Procurement',	'mcms',	'94',	'2011-02-04',	'',	'',	'',	'bps-content.php?cid=134',	NULL,	'',	'13:13:36',	115,	0,	'',	''),
(184,	'Development Finance and Procurement',	'<p>Manages the administration of the Unit of the Botswana Police Service ensuring that budgeting, procurement, disbursement, administration and management of Supplies of the Botswana Police Service recurrent budget below the line accounts are done properly and in accordance with the regulations and procedures and in a way to achieve the goals and objectives. It is also responsible for the planning, development and maintenance of the entire Botswana Police Service Estate and Facilities as well as ensuring that police officers are issued with uniform and stationery.<p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The branch is formed by following Units;</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Development and Planning</li>\r\n<li>Finance</li>\r\n<li>Quarter Master and Procurement</li></ul>',	'Development Finance and Procurement',	'mcms',	'182',	'2011-02-04',	NULL,	'Active',	NULL,	'bps-content.php?cid=184',	NULL,	NULL,	'14:29:46',	0,	0,	NULL,	NULL),
