(229,	'Department of Management Services',	'<p>The Chaplaincy programme has been  introduced to provide spiritual guidance and support to BPS employees and their  dependents, regardless of their religious affiliation. <strong>Our mission </strong>in this programme  is to provide opportunities for spiritual and moral growth of the Botswana  Police Service employees and their dependents with a view to create a ministry  of care, support and presence to the employees. Through the <strong>Return-to-work programme, </strong>the  Chaplaincy Section<strong> </strong>facilitates the  earliest possible return of ill employees to productive work within their  physical capabilities. This is achieved through modified duty allocated to the  individual as part of the employee normal duties are changed to accommodate  temporary physical and mental limitations. Based on this account, Chaplain and  Chaplain Assistants have the responsibility to visit and pray with all  employees who are either confined to the hospital or are on a long sick leave  within their areas of operation.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>For further information contact: </strong><br />\r\nOccupational Health,  Safety, Chaplaincy and Social Welfare Unit<br />\r\nBotswana Police Service<br />\r\nPhone: 3951161/3622044/3622114/3622253&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />\r\nFax: 3973723</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',	'Department of Management Services',	'mcms',	'228',	'2011-02-10',	NULL,	'Active',	NULL,	'bps-content.php?cid=229',	NULL,	NULL,	'09:56:49',	0,	0,	NULL,	NULL),
