(410,	'Special Support Group',	'<h3>HISTORY</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Special Support Group (SSG) is a para-military  Branch of the Botswana Police Service (BPS)</li>\r\n    <li>It was formed in 1978 when the Police Mobile Unit  (PMU) that existed then was disbanded to form the nuclear of the Botswana  Defence Force (BDF) in 1977.&nbsp;</li>\r\n    <li>SSG was born with a total strength of thirty-four  (34) officers of different ranks.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul type=\\\"disc\\\">\r\n    <li>Its strength increased by 121 between 1980 and 1983 and increased       to 569 between 1984 and 1991, to 807 between 1991 and 1994 and reduced to       676 between 1995 and 2007 due to different factors like resignations,       dismissals, retirement and deaths.</li>\r\n    <li>In 1990 it was transformed into companies, platoons and sections       for easy command and control.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>FUNCTIONS</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>SSG provides  operational support to Divisions, Districts and Stations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>SSG COMPANIES</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Provides operational support to Divisions,  Districts and Stations by providing Operational and Specialist services.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>OPERATIONAL SERVICES</h3>\r\n<ul type=\\\"disc\\\">\r\n    <li>Mobile and foot patrols</li>\r\n    <li>Escort/shipment of revenue and minerals</li>\r\n    <li>Escort of hardened criminals from State Prison to places of trial</li>\r\n    <li>VIP Protection</li>\r\n    <li>Border Patrols</li>\r\n    <li>Crime surveillance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>SPECIALISED SERVICES</h3>\r\n<ul type=\\\"disc\\\">\r\n    <li>Rescue operations</li>\r\n    <li>Public order operations</li>\r\n    <li>Tracking operations</li>\r\n    <li>Narcotic searches</li>\r\n    <li>Weapon training, field craft and tactics</li>\r\n    <li>Ceremonial and funeral services</li>\r\n    <li>Conduct undercover overt and covert operations</li>\r\n    <li>Peace Keeping Missions</li>\r\n    <li>Disposal of explosives like bombs</li>\r\n    <li>Provision of security at political meetings, sports activities and       demonstrations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>SAFER BUSINESS</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The Branch patrols all business areas.</li>\r\n    <li>It provides escorts for individual businesses  and government revenues after a formal request &nbsp;lodged with the Commander</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>SAFER COMMUNITY</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The branch provides escorts for members of the  public where it is suspected that the community might be at risk of attack from  criminals.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>SCUBA DIVERS</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Search victims during drowning incidents</li>\r\n    <li>Rescues the nation during floods period</li>\r\n    <li>Trains officers as divers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>CONTACT US</h3>\r\n<h3>PHYSICAL ADDRESS</h3>\r\n<h3>POSTAL ADDRESS</h3>\r\n<p>The Commander Special Support Group<br />\r\nP O Box 40116 <br />\r\nGaborone <br />\r\nFax: 3903305</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>SSG TELEPHONE DIRECTORY</h3>\r\n<p>Switchboard&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; =&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3957272<br />\r\nCommander (w)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3912081<br />\r\nDeputy Commander (w)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; =&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3914390<br />\r\nDirector of Music (w)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; =&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3903334</p>',	'Special Support Group',	'mcms',	'182',	'2011-03-14',	'',	'',	'',	'bps-content.php?cid=410',	NULL,	'',	'10:32:06',	186,	0,	'',	''),
(411,	'Special Support Group',	'<p>Special Support Group (SSG) is a para-military Branch of the Botswana Police Service (BPS). It was formed in 1978 when the Police Mobile Unit (PMU) that existed then was disbanded to form the nuclear of the Botswana Defence Force (BDF) in 1977. SSG was born with a total strength of thirty-four (34) officers of different ranks. In 1990 it was transformed into companies, platoons and sections for easy command and control. It provides operational support to Divisions, Districts and Stations by;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Mobile and foot patrols </li>\r\n<li>Escort/shipment of revenue and minerals </li>\r\n<li>Escort of hardened criminals from State Prison to places of trial </li>\r\n<li>VIP Protection </li>\r\n<li>Border Patrols </li>\r\n<li>Crime surveillance </li>\r\n<li>Provision of security at political meetings, sports activities and demonstrations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>It also compliments with the following specialized services</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Public order operations </li>\r\n<li>Tracking operations </li>\r\n<li>Narcotic searches </li>\r\n<li>Peace Keeping Missions </li>\r\n<li>Disposal of explosives like bombs </li>\r\n<li>Rescue operations</li>\r\n<li>Scuba divers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>POSTAL ADDRESS</h3>\r\n<p>The Commander Special Support Group<br/>\r\nP O Box 40116 <br/>\r\nGaborone <br/>\r\nFax: 3903305<br/></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>SSG TELEPHONE DIRECTORY</h3>\r\n<p>Switchboard = 3957272<br/>\r\nCommander(w) = 3912081<br/>\r\nDeputy Commander(w) = 3914390<br/>\r\nDirector of Music (w) = 3903334<br/>\r\n</p>',	'Special Support Group',	'mcms',	'182',	'2011-03-14',	'',	'Active',	'',	'bps-content.php?cid=411',	NULL,	'',	'10:34:56',	187,	0,	'',	''),
(470,	'Air Support Services',	'<p>Air Support Branch was formed in January 2009 to address the increasing crime and road accidents to enhance efficiency and effectiveness of the Botswana Police Service operations around the country. Its functions are;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Prevention and Investigation operation</li>\r\n    <li>Rapid response to crime incidents</li>\r\n    <li>Rapid deployment of personnel</li>\r\n    <li>Aerial photographs and videos</li>\r\n    <li>Monitoring of public gatherings and big events</li>\r\n    <li>Borderline operations and patrols</li>\r\n    <li>Vehicle pursuits</li>\r\n    <li>Suspect pursuits</li>\r\n    <li>Roof top searches</li>\r\n    <li>Searching for missing persons</li>\r\n    <li>Critical incidents /disaster management (rescue)</li>\r\n    <li>Support and work with other branches within the Botswana Police Service to execute the following duties:\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>To provide rapid response, tactical insight and airborne policing services.</li>\r\n        <li>To provide systematic method of crime prevention and detection.</li>\r\n        <li>To support national efforts in protecting life and property.</li>\r\n        <li>To provide supporting services in maintaining public safety and tranquility.</li>\r\n        <li>To enhance police visibility and capability in maintaining public safety.</li>\r\n        <li>To provide support in investigation and evidence gathering.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><h3>The Units under Air  Support are:</h3><br />\r\nEngineering Unit<br />\r\nFlight Crew Unit<br />\r\nOperations Unit</p>\r\n<p><h3>Air Support Branch Contact Details</h3><br />\r\nThe Office of the Director<br />\r\nAdministration &amp; Accounts<br />\r\nTel: 3915388<br />\r\nFax: 3973723<br />\r\nPostal Address: P/Bag SK8<br />\r\nGaborone<br />\r\nLocated: BPS Head Quarters</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><h3>Deputy Directors Office</h3><br />\r\nEngineering, Flight Crew &amp; Operations<br />\r\nTel:&nbsp; 3915 208<br />\r\nFax: 3915189<br />\r\nPostal Address: P/Bag SK8<br />\r\nGaborone</p>',	'Air Support Services',	'mcms',	'182',	'2011-04-14',	'',	'Active',	'',	'bps-content.php?cid=470',	NULL,	'',	'13:09:03',	0,	0,	'',	''),
(413,	'Criminal Investigations Department',	'<ul>\r\n    <li>The Criminal Investigation Department (CID) is a Branch  in the Botswana Police Service which is headed by a Director.</li>\r\n    <li>The Branch prevents and detects crime and is responsible  for the investigation of serious crimes.</li>\r\n    <li>CID consists of specialised units such as Serious  Crime Squad, Diamond and Narcotics Squad, Crime Prevention Unit, National  Central Bureau (NCB) Interpol. The Branch has establishment at Stations,  Districts and Divisions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Serious Crime Squad</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The Unit is headed by an Officer Commanding holding  the rank of Senior Superintendent</li>\r\n    <li>It is responsible for motor vehicle theft, motor  vehicle clearance and fraud related investigations. Motor vehicle clearance services  are currently done at the Serious Crime Squad (Gaborone)  Lobatse, Ghanzi, Maun, Francistown,  Selibe-Phikwe, Serowe, Mahalapye, Tsabong and Kasane. The offices issue Southern  African Regional Police Chiefs Cooperation Organization (SARPCCO) clearances  for vehicle movement within the SADC region if the vehicle originates from one  member country to another. This arrangement helps both the customers and the  individual Police Services from issuing duplicitous documentation for the  movement of the same vehicle across transitory countries.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Diamond and Narcotics Squad</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The Unit curbs crime related to diamonds, and the  illicit use or dealing in any type of narcotics.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Crime Prevention Unit</h3>\r\n<p>The Unit  educates the public on crime prevention issues and coordinates initiatives such  as Neighbourhood Watch Schemes and Cluster committees It provides tips on how to  secure property and on personal safety</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Interpol National Bureau</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>As a member of the International Police Organisation, the  unit links Botswana Police Service with 185 other Police organizations around  the globe through a closed and secure communication system called i24/7.</li>\r\n    <li>Any information sought from any member country can be  availed immediately throughout the system.</li>\r\n    <li>Other Law Enforcement Departments like Immigration,  Customs, DCEC etc benefit immensely from the i24/7 facility.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Divisional CID</h3>\r\n<p>The  CID Branch works hand in hand with General Duty Branch. The Divisional CID  Officers oversees Districts CID Units under their jurisdiction and the  Districts oversee the Station CID units.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Contact Details</h3>\r\n<p>Director of  Criminal Investigation Department<br />\r\nPhone: 3914706</p>\r\n<p>Fax: 3952651<br />\r\nBox 1082, Gaborone</p>\r\n<p>Enquiries:  3642300</p>',	'Criminal Investigations Department',	'mcms',	'189',	'2011-03-14',	'',	'',	'',	'bps-content.php?cid=413',	NULL,	'',	'10:41:43',	191,	0,	'',	''),
